      • setLogLevel

        public static void setLogLevel(int newLogLevel)
        Sets the logging level to the absolute value of newLogLevel. The logging level determines which log statements are printed to System.out or System.err. All log messages are written to the log file regardless of the logging level. The default value is LEVEL_DEBUG, indicating that debug messages, warnings, errors, and terminal failures should all be printed.
        Parameters:
        newLogLevel - the new log level. A value greater/equal to LEVEL_DEBUG will print all messages. A value of LEVEL_WARN will print only warnings, errors, and terminal errors. A value of LEVEL_ERR or less will only print errors and terminal failures. A value of LEVEL_TERM will only print terminal failures.
